cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on improving monocular depth estimation by mitigating the synthetic-real domain shift. This is a problem that is commonly addressed in the computer vision community, which falls under the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel attentional module that learns to identify and remove out-of-domain regions in real images, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing image translation models, which falls under the cs.GR sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method to improve depth estimation, which is a task that is commonly addressed in the robotics community, falling under the cs.RO sub-category.
